Description: Sherd from shoulder of pottery transport amphora; incised inscription. Thick wall; highly micaceous brown clay with grey core.
Curator's comments: The fabric would seem to be local and probably not pre-Ptolemaic; but the graffito seems earlier. M. Pesenti suggests Clazomenian production.
